narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: In exploring historiographical approaches to the twelfth century, I believe that I have learned to better assess the narratives books sometimes build around medieval history.
Great knowledge of twelfth century historiography. This class displayed the interpretive variety in looking at a certain period of history. Good example of the problem of periodization.
Deeper knowledge of historiographic perspectives of the 12th Century as a concept. Critical thought on how contemporary events shapes our views on history.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I thought the reading was really interesting and worked together well as a whole. I especially enjoyed the weeks in which we were assigned chapters to report back on. It ensured that had everyone an opportunity to speak in class.

Great course with a great professor. I loved all of the readings, or at least thought that they were all beneficial. The class discussion was very good as well. I saw no real weaknesses. One of my favorite courses.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, I would recommend this course to another student. I really enjoyed the course and the discussion was always interesting and challenging.

Professor Freedman is extremely helpful in and out of class, and is a great facilitator of discussion. The subject matter was extremely interesting and the twelfth century is fascinating. I would totally recommend this course to anyone interested in history at all.
I would recommend this class not only to historians of the middle ages but of all epochs. In a sense it was also a class on the 20th century and its historiography.
